---
title: Spinach Ricotta Ravioli with Salmon plus Zucchini Ribbons, Tomato & Creamy Lemon Sauce
description: Tender ravioli are pretty much good in any form, but they’re especially great when packed with fresh spinach and creamy ricotta. This rendition is “dragged through the garden,” majorly amping up the veggie factor. Loaded with chopped and ribboned zucchini, diced tomato, and a bevy of Italian herbs and spices. It’s taken to the next level with a creamy lemon sauce, nutty Parmesan, and a sprinkle of scallion greens. Be still, our pasta-loving hearts...
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/63ebfad3ef19ef6c2207adee-ed74e840.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65a8291cee7b8a986cc22373.pdf
cuisine: Italian
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 15 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spinach-ricotta-ravioli-with-salmon-65a8291cee7b8a986cc22373
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 900 kcal
  fat: 55 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 53 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 47 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 860 mg
---

Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim ends from @zucchini{1%unit}; shave zucchini lengthwise into thin ribbons
using a #peeler{}, rotating as you go, until you get to the seedy core. Finely
chop core.

Dice @tomato{1%unit}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating
whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1%unit}.

Once water is boiling, gently add @spinach and ricotta ravioli{9%ounce} to
#pot{}. Immediately reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
al dente and floating to the top, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

> TIP: Gently shake strainer with ravioli in it to remove as much moisture as
> possible.

Pat @skin-on salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add salmon (skin sides down); cook until skin is crisp,
~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.
Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add chopped zucchini, tomato, scallion whites, and
@Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}. Cook until veggies are just softened,
~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use 2 tsp Italian Seasoning; use the rest as you like.

> Use pan used for chicken or salmon here.

Reduce heat under pan with veggies to medium, then stir in
@veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water, and a
squeeze of lemon juice. Reduce heat to low and cook, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted and
combined. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until
> sauce reaches a creamy consistency.

Separate zucchini ribbons with your hands, then stir into pan with sauce.

Gently stir in drained ravioli. Simmer until sauce has thickened,
~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in lemon zest to taste.

Divide pasta between plates. Garnish with scallion greens and
@parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon!). Serve chicken or salmon atop
> pasta.